h3. Problem Definition
Currently when you configure the maximum resources option under the plan configuration, the description stated the following:
{panel}
The maximum number of team members which can work on a story simultaneously.
{panel}
The above description can be misleading as in the simultaneously aspect is not necessarily true - while normally stages are not being worked on in parallel, disabling the Stage/sprint constraint might cause stages to be scheduled in parallel and hence two people would be working on different stages but in parallel.

h3. Suggested Solution
Rephrase the description for this option to better explain the intended configuration and expected behaviour.

